The Chronicle Oliver Kazunga, Senior Business Reporter ZIMBABWE Miners Federation (ZMF) president, Ms Henrietta Rushwaya, has been re-elected as the federation’s president for the next five years. This follows the recent ZMF national elections. Speaking by telephone, the federation spokesperson Mr Dosman Mangisi said Ms Rushwaya together with three other national executive members have retained their positions. “Ms Rushwaya together with three other national executive members have retained their positions. Mr Marufu Sithole as the vice president, Mr Morgan Mugawu as the secretary general and Mr Lufeyi Shato treasury general have won the elections unopposed,” he said. -@okazunga